Rating: 4
These stuffed mushrooms are the best! I've made them a bunch of times and everyone goes junkie on them. I agree with others that cutting the cream cheese down to 6-7 ounces, using fresh garlic, and pre-roasting the caps for 10 minutes improves them, plus I have found that the flavours only get better the next day or even the day after that. It's a perfect do-way-ahead dish, (stuff the caps right before baking and forget about the wine - I've only ever remembered that step twice and it makes no difference), and if you drizzle the olive oil across the assembled caps instead of coating the dish, they are even better. Two very enthusiastic thumbs up!

Rating: 3
Great party appetizer b/c they can be made ahead and are very tasty. I made this for xmas & new years parties both following the recipe as is and modifying it. The modified version is much better: roast the mushrooms first (as others commented) to dewater them and reduce reheating time; use 1/2 the cream cheese; chop some parsley and add to the mix, to lighten them up; use fresh garlic (I used 3-4 cloves minced). I used large mushrooms from Costco.

Rating: 0
I've made this a few times and although I thought they were good, I also found something lacking in the consistency of the stuffing. It was too much like oozing cream cheese with chunks of sausage in it. So, I decided to make the following changes: 1) Once the sausage was cooked, I minced it on a cutting board. 2) I decreased the amount of cream cheese by 1/4. 3) I increased the parmesan (I actually used italian blend shredded cheese) by 1/4. 4) I added 1/3 cup (or so) of bread crumbs. Overall, I thought it was much better and so did my test audience. I had read that some people thought the taste was one dimensional and these changes helped.

