After reading some of the reviews, I felt I had to chime in. I have been making these since finding the recipe a few years back on this site. These are fantastic - if you follow the recipe. Do not attempt to "lighten" or substitute - they will not be the same. As for those who have commented that the recipe is missing something...it must be the type of sausage you're using. You need to use traditional hot Italian sausage - pork - not turkey or chicken. I live in WNY and our area produces outstanding Italian sausage. Perhaps that's the problem with some of the reviewers? Hope this helps.

