These were amazing! This will now become my stuffed mushroom staple. A few things changed based on other people's reviews: I used both medium sized button mushrooms and bella mushrooms to try out. I added a few drops of wine in the caps and let sit, and brushed over as well. I chopped up fresh garlic and the stems of both the button and bella mushrooms, and cooked with the sausage and oregano. I seasoned the meat with a little salt and pepper too. Also, 8 oz of cream cheese is a lot. I reduced to 6 oz, and maybe next time might reduce to 5. I also used more sausage than called for (used Jimmy Dean sausage). I also added chopped sun-dried tomatoes in oil (a must!!! Just drained on paper towels to reduce oil). The freshly grated parmesean cheese made such a difference too. Very cheesy, so keep that in mind. My boyfriend absolutley loved them and wanted more. I am making more for a dinner party tonight (already prepped and ready to go!)

