Rating: 3
I made this recipe for a large reception (400 people) and it was great. I've played around with it a bit and found a few tidbits. 1. Mushrooms render alot of water when heated. When the water mixes with the filling, it can make the middle soggy. Now I prebake the mushrooms for a few minutes and pour off some of the liquid. I'm still working on an easier solution. 2. You really don't need the egg. the cream cheese binds everything together nicely. 3. Mixing sweet and hot sausage together gives just enough zing without making them too hot. 4. Mushrooms aren't meant to sit in a heated chafing dish for long. When I made these for the reception, they ended up sitting in chafing dishes longer than I anticipated. They still tasted good, but they definitely didn't look that great.

Rating: 4
Delicious! Guests raved

