Rating: 4
I have made these for a Christmas party for 2 years now, and everyone loves them. For those who think that this is too rich, try cutting down on the amount of cream cheese you use. Just add enough so that the mixture holds together - this should decrease the "heaviness". I use about 1/3 to 1/2 of the cream cheese that is called for and omit the egg yolk and wine, and they are still awesome. It's nice that these can be assembled a day ahead, then cooked when needed. I liked the idea of a previous reviewer who sauteed the mushrooms, added to the sausage mixture, then put into phyllo cups - I might have to try this next time as a change!

