Rating: 4
This is an excellent appetizer for a party. Be sure and look through the reviews. I generally make this by using about 3/4 lb. hot sausage and 1/4 lb. sweet sausage per recipe -- but about 6 oz. light cream cheese instead of a full 8-oz. package. This doubles very well. I start off by melon balling the caps (use 1" size -- these are easier to eat when bite size!)and letting them marinate in the wine -- it's easier than brushing it on and the wine adds a nice flavor. When sauteeing the sausage, I add 2-3 cloves minced garlic, some finely chopped onion, and add dried tarragon. I also use closer to one cup Parm for the filling, and add some of the wine also. Great to prepare ahead as indicated in the recipe, but bring the dish to room temp before baking. Prepare for lots of compliments!!

